In web development, accessibility refers to the practice of designing and building websites & applications which can be used by everyone, including people with disabilities.
The objective is to ensure that all users — regardless of ability — can perceive, understand, navigate, and interact with the web.
Accessibility helps for people with disability to utlize web content with ease (e.g. Users with Visual impairments, Hearing impairments, Motor disabilities, Cognitive limitations & Color blindness.
Developing digital content with Accessibility considerations helps in following ways:
1. Inclusive and equal access to information/content
2. Legal compliance across globe
3. Improved Usability for All uses
4. SEO (search engine optmization) benefits
5. Achieves Social responsibility 
